  <refnamediv>
    <refname>graph_center</refname>
    <refpurpose> center of a graph</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>[no,rad] = graph_center(g)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Parameters</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>g</term>
        <listitem>
          <para> a <link linkend="graph_data_structure">graph_data_structure</link>.</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>no</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>integer</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>rad</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>integer</para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para><literal>graph_center</literal> computes a center of the graph <literal>g</literal> i.e. the 
    node for which the largest of the shortest paths to all the other nodes 
    is minimum. The lengths of the arcs are supposed to be integer (and the default
    value is 1). 
    The output is the value <literal>rad</literal> of the length of the radius and
    <literal>no</literal> which is the node number of the center of the graph.</para>
  </refsection>
